fcitx5-sinsebeolsik-p2 (0.1.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Backspace polish: preserve single-key jongs, restore frozen virtual
    jung after jong/jung removal so re-pressing the same vowel re-composes
    (e.g. joc → 웨 → BS → 우(virtual ㅜ) → f → 웊).
  * Right-hand symbol layer: shifted right-hand keys (H/J/K/L/M/N/U/Y/P,
    Shift+', Shift+Z) emit literal codepoints (□ ' " · … ― ; ○ × / ㆍ)
    per the .ist simulator spec. Shift+I/O are absorbed (empty slot).
  * Internal QWERTY re-translation via libxkbcommon: engine now keeps its
    own xkb_state with a US QWERTY keymap and re-evaluates each printable
    keystroke's hardware keycode through it before keymap.toml lookup, so
    the IME works correctly on hosts using non-QWERTY system XKB layouts
    (Canary, Dvorak, Colemak, …). Falls back to original keysym if
    libxkbcommon initialization fails — QWERTY hosts behave identically.
  * Engine cosmetic: tray label 신P2 → 한, monochrome icon name.

 -- Bogamie <bogamie02@gmail.com>  Sat, 02 May 2026 02:15:00 +0900

fcitx5-sinsebeolsik-p2 (0.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Bundle setup-fcitx5-trigger.sh as /usr/bin/sinsebeolsik-p2-setup-trigger
    so .deb users can register the Hangul keysym in fcitx5 without cloning
    the repo or curling a script from GitHub.

 -- Bogamie <bogamie02@gmail.com>  Fri, 01 May 2026 20:30:00 +0900

fcitx5-sinsebeolsik-p2 (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Hangul automaton with Sinsebeolsik P2 simulator-verified behavior:
    no dokkaebibul, no auto-IEUNG, no jong cluster splitting on next vowel,
    real-vs-virtual jung distinction, ssang-jaeum via doubled cho keystroke.
  * TOML-driven keymap loadable from
    ~/.local/share/fcitx5/sinsebeolsik-p2/sinsebeolsik_p2.toml
    or /usr/share/fcitx5/sinsebeolsik-p2/sinsebeolsik_p2.toml,
    with embedded fallback compiled in.
  * Helper script setup-fcitx5-trigger.sh registers the Hangul keysym
    as a global IM trigger.

 -- Bogamie <bogamie02@gmail.com>  Fri, 01 May 2026 00:00:00 +0900
